data.description: MOTIVATED SELLER.   10 ACRES. If room to roam is what you are looking for, maybe a mini farm, or just lots of peace and quiet, this spacious 4 bedroom  should be in your radar.  All appliances stay.  AC is only 3 years old.  Septic and drain field are approximately 6 years old. Plenty of room for gardening, animals and furry friends and of course the all important ''off road'' toys. There is a creek towards the back of the property that would make a great camping spot. Front half of property is high and in flood zone X as seen in the new survey in documents section.  No flood insurance required per surveyor.  There is a fenced pasture for horses .  To the right of the driveway is a large chicken coop that housed lots of chickens. The back half slopes towards the creek.  Come see what could be your next home in the country with lots of potential. Seller will pay $10,000 towards buyers closing cost with accepted contract.
